10:31 AM Prosecuting attorney Craig Lambert appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Christian D Pagan appeared in court, Attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow for Christian D Pagan appeared in court. 
Jacob Maxson appears by video, is sworn and questioned by Attorney Lambert. He is a police officer with the Marshfield Police Department. On 1/22/22, he attempted to stop a vehicle driven by defendant. He observed a vehicle traveling at a high rate of speed without its lights on. He activated his lights and siren and the vehicle accelerated. The vehicle eventually did stop in the parking lot in his apartment complex. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. 
Attorney Zamzow cross-examines witness. 
Attorney Lambert redirects.
Attorney Zamzow cross-examines witness.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Defendant stands mute and Court enters plea of not guilty. Bond is continued.
Final pre-trial scheduled for May 27, 2022 at 10:00 am.
